Base Attributes¶

Description for basic attributes to be added here

Source Code¶

This module includes a class which defines basic attributes and methods for the Data Explorer, Preprocessor and FeatureBuilder and all their custom classes. The respective modules import this class and inherit from it

__init__(data_source: Union[str, pandas.core.frame.DataFrame], target_name: str = '', features: Union[str, Sequence, None] = None)[source]¶

Initialization function for Basic Data Attributes.

Parameters

  • data_source (str or pd.DataFrame) – a string with a file containing Data or a pandas DataFrame to be read.

  • target_name – optionally specify the target_name column within the data set

  • features – optionally pre define features which are to be kept upon initialization

ingest(**options: Mapping[str]) → BasicDataAttributes[source]¶

Ingests the data source provided in the attribute and derives a pandas DataFrame out of it. The following data source are possible:

  • csv files

  • json files

  • parquet files

  • pickle files

  • pandas DataFrame

When the data source is a string containing a pointer to a file, the respective file is read. If it is however a pandas DataFrame, the data is kept in a DataFrame.

The pandas DataFrame is saved into the input attribute

Returns
